Going off at a tangent (as ever) we cannot recall reading many enquiries
from the US about writing slopes (A.K.A writing boxes). Don't you have
them? or are they uncommon?

In what is now the UK every middle class household had one and often it
seems every adult member of that household.

If you are not sure what we are referring to they are usually featured
in Millars or Lyle's Christmas annuals.

One of the first Urban Legends that J-H came across when he started
dealing in the early seventies was about these boxes. It went thus- 'a
friend of a friend bought two slopes in Auction. When he got home he
discovered that one of them had a secret drawer inside that opened with
a spring mechanism (not uncommon). He opened it up to find some Gold
Coins.' He never did meet that friend of a friend and is convinced it
was a marketing ploy by unscrupulous auctioneers to drum up business
when writing boxes were two a penny. For our opinions on the scruples of
auctioneers please refer to earlier postings.
